html:
princes of Zoan are become fools. Officers and leaders of Zoan (19:11) and Noph (or Memphis, once Egypt's capital during the Old Kingdom), have lost their ability to lead. They act more like fools than true leaders, perhaps due to self- deception.

they have also seduced Egypt. The thoughtless leaders and governors of Egypt's provinces lead the citizens astray with their wickedness and deceptions.
